    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Quilting technique in which layers of cloth with no filling between them are back-stitched together under sufficient tension so as to raise the ground very slightly, thus giving the impression of filling.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Técnica de acolchado en la cual capas de tela sin relleno entre sí son cosidas juntas con suficiente tensión de modo de levantarse ligeramente sobre el fondo, dando la impresión de relleno.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Doorstiktechniek waarbij lagen stof zonder vulling ertussen met achtersteek zijn genaaid, en waarbij de spanning zodanig is dat de bovenlaag iets is toegegeven ten opzichte van de onderlaag, wat een indruk geeft van vulling.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>兩層布料之間無填充物，以拉緊針腳的回針縫方式讓面料微微隆起，製造出填充料效果的拼布技術。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
